race.description: Jarrod Arentz Electrical/Solar Solutions Mdn Plt
race.comment: QUEEN CHRISTINE (9) did a good job coming from the back at Ballarat on debut and then started in red figures at Warrnambool but lacked a knockout punch on the heavy track beaten 2.3L. She's sure to be fitter and jumps from the paint with Coffey aboard. The one to beat.   ISTRIANO (2) debuts for the smart McEvoy yard and they get them going early. Won a recent jumpout at Murtoa and John Allen stays aboard. Should race boldly and can threaten. APACHE SUNRISE (5) resumes and her effort at Seymour two back stacks right up. She won a recent jumpout and can come back better. Will get every chance from an inside barrier. CAPE RADSTOCK (7) debuts and won his latest jumpout. Maps well and Yendall is a key jockey booking. A canny stable and keep onside.
